-- Taiwan's HTC July sales fall 45 percent on year
-- 
-- Mon Aug 6, 2012 3:20am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/08/06/us-htc-sales-idUSBRE87509K20120806

 

 TAIPEI  (Reuters) - Taiwan smartphone maker HTC Corp ( 2498.TW ) said on Monday that unaudited consolidated sales for July were T$25 billion ($834 million), down 45 percent from the same month a year earlier. 
 The monthly sales compared with T$45.11 billion a year ago and T$30 billion in the previous month. It did not give further details. ($1 = 29.9760 Taiwan dollars) (Reporting by Clare Jim; Editing by Ed Lane)